<span class="textbold_orange">Species Reactivity</span><br />
We first determine the test compound’s reactivity with different species. In this example, the species tested were human (MDA-MB-231), mouse (NIH-3T3), and rat (RBL-2H3). Here we use Tumor necrosis factor alpha (TNF-&alpha;) as an example test compound. In a sterile, black 96-well plate, MDA-MB-231, NIH-3T3, and RBL-2H3 cells were plated at a cell density of 20,000 cells per well and allowed to adhere overnight. The next day, the culture medium was removed and replaced with medium dosed with 10 ng/mL TNF-&alpha; or no TNF-&alpha; for the baseline controls. The dosed culture medium was prepared from a stock solution of 10,000 ng/mL TNF-&alpha; in dH2O. Triplicate wells were incubated for 10 minutes with the TNF-&alpha; or control medium. The pNF&kappa;B and total protein was then quantified using the NF&kappa;B Phosphorylation Assay Kit (EFNKB-100). The pNF&kappa;B values were normalized to the total protein content of the sample. The relative increase in pNF&kappa;B for the cells treated with TNF-&alpha; was 3.64:1, 2.96:1, and 0.83:1 for MDA-MB-231, NIH-3T3, and RBL-2H3 respectively. The cell line MDA-MB-231 showed the greatest reactivity to the test compound TNF-&alpha; and was chosen as the cell line for the next experiments.
<br /><br />
<div><img src="/images/NFKB.Phosphorylation.Status.Screening.Service1.jpg" width="450" height="250" alt="ERK Phosphorylation Titration"></div><br /><br />

<span class="textbold_orange">Phosphorylation Titration</span><br />
To determine the time course of NF&kappa;B phosphorylation, first a titration was run on the concentration of the test compound; here we use TNF-&alpha; as an example. In a sterile, black 96-well plate, MDA-MB-231 cells were plated at a cell density of 20,000 cells per well and allowed to adhere overnight. The next day, the culture medium was removed and replaced with medium dosed with TNF-&alpha; at the following concentrations: 0.0E+0, 3.8E-4, 1.5E-3, 6.1E-3, 2.4E-2, 9.8E-2, 3.9E-1, 1.6E+0, 6.3E+0, 2.5E+1, 1.0E+2, and 4.0E+2 ng/mL. The dosed culture medium was prepared from a stock solution of 10,000 ng/mL TNF-&alpha; in dH2O. Triplicate wells were incubated for 20 minutes with the TNF-&alpha;. The pNF&kappa;B and total protein was then quantified using the NF&kappa;B Phosphorylation Assay Kit (ENFKB-100). The pNF&kappa;B values were normalized to the total protein content of the sample. 
<br /><br />
<div><img src="/images/NFKB.Phosphorylation.Status.Screening.Service2.jpg" width="350" height="250" alt="ERK Phosphorylation Kinetics"></div><br /><br />

<span class="textbold_orange">Phosphorylation Kinetics</span><br />
After the titration on the test compound concentration, we measure the NF&kappa;B phosphorylation kinetics for a specific dosage. TNF-&alpha; will continue to serve as our example here; we measure the NF&kappa;B phosphorylation kinetics for TNF-&alpha; at a concentration of 100 ng/mL. In a sterile, black 96-well plate, PANC-1 cells were plated at a cell density of 20,000 cells per well and allowed to adhere overnight. The next day, the culture medium was removed and replaced with 100 ng/mL TNF-&alpha; dosed medium. The dosed culture medium was prepared from a stock solution of 10,000 ng/mL TNF-&alpha; in dH2O. Triplicate wells were incubated for 0, 2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 15, 20, 30, 40, 60, and 120 minutes with the TNF-&alpha. The pNF&kappa;B and total protein was then quantified using the NF&kappa;B Phosphorylation Assay Kit (ENFKB-100). The pNF&kappa;B values were normalized to the total protein content of the sample. The 0 minutes (no TNF-&alpha; incubation) served as the untreated control for basal NF&kappa;B phosphorylation.
